oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Copy print of photographic postcard, "The Death de Quentin Roosevelt."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Copy print of a photographic postcard depicting the death scene of Quentin Roosevelt, taken 10 minutes after the accident. Shows crumpled airplane and Roosevelt's body in the foreground. Roosevelt was a member of the 95th Aero Squadron, killed July 14, 1918. The aircraft displays a painted "kicking mule" squadron insignia and the number "14." Quentin was the youngest son of President Teddy Roosevelt and First Lady Edith Roosevelt.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Roosevelt, Quentin
